room in the hotel. And a very serious talk with her daughter. An unthinkable marriage, a most idiotic venture. But despite all this she was flattered that Luzhin had so earnestly and old-fashionedly addressed himself to her first.

'It's happened, congratulations,' she said that evening to her daughter. 'Don't look so innocent, you understand perfectly well. Our friend wishes to marry.'

'I'm sorry he told you,' replied her daughter. 'It concerns only him and me.'

